  "body": "It seems https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/pull/4734 uses `NETHERMIND_MININGCONFIG_EXTRADATA` to set extra data for blocks built post merge. This is confusing to me because:\r\n- There is no mining post merge, yet the configuration is under the Mining module.\r\n- `NETHERMIND_MININGCONFIG_ENABLED` defaults to `false`. Does a post merge validator also need to set this explicitly to `true`?\r\n    - If yes, it seems like a bad default: will consensus layer clients not receive execution layer blocks from Nethermind?\r\n    - If not, it seems weird for any other setting (namely the ExtraData) to be active if the Mining module as a whole is \"disabled\".\r\n\r\nPerhaps the docs in https://docs.nethermind.io/nethermind/ethereum-client/configuration/mining could clarify the relevancy and behavior of the Mining module in post merge world?",
